The paper deals with designing a robust sensor to defend against attackers with malicious control objectives. This involves game-theoretic concepts and optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of control systems (cs.SY), game theory (cs.GT), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to design the sensor outputs, which falls under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
